The essence of information studies, its object and concepts; its relations to the other disciplines. The development of information studies, main research areas, problems and researchers. Main approaches to information society and the essence of informational infrastructure of society.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Introduction of main knowledge to information studies. To give an overview of the field as a research and practice area. Main concepts, theories and research areas.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, a student has an overview of the field of information studies; s/he knows its place in relation to the other disciplines. Student knows the terminology, main theories and methodologies of the field; s/he has an overview of the development of information studies, its main research areas, problems, researchers and approaches to information society. Student understands the role of information worker in a society; s/he knows the competency requirements to an information specialist, is familiar to the situation of education on the field and speciality organisations.
